HEADWORD: Flirt-gill
<hw>Flirt"-gill`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A woman of light
behavior; a gill-flirt.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You heard him take me up like a <qex>flirt-gill</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Beau. & Fl.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flirtigig</ent>⟦br⟧
